ğŸ§ª Testing & Validation
Stress & Corruption Testing

Lichen OS emphasizes failure behavior, not just success cases.

Tested scenarios include:

1M+ valid FC-496 cells

Random 1â€“3 bit corruptions

Network interruption simulations

Sustained CPU and memory pressure

Observed results:

High detection rate of corrupted cells

Graceful degradation under load

No silent data acceptance during corruption

These results indicate robustness, not perfection.

ğŸ’¡ Intended Use Cases (Exploratory)

Lichen OS is not production-ready, but may be useful for research in:

resilient data storage

distributed sensing

AI system alignment metrics

long-lived autonomous systems

Claims are limited to controlled experimental contexts.

ğŸ“Œ Project Philosophy

Detectability over denial

Structure over heuristics

Metrics over intuition

Resilience over optimization

Lichen OS does not attempt to â€œsolve AI ethicsâ€ or â€œreplace existing operating systems.â€
It explores how far structure alone can go in reducing ambiguity and silent failure.

